social_posts.post_text:
I love it when I hide things on myself :) 
—
A few summers ago here in Jackson, playing 18 @tetonpines with @austinrhopkins @natty.schneider & @koldnsnowin, I hit a hole-in-one on the par 3 7th hole, 160 yards from the pin swinging from the umbrella marked, set back and lake clearance mandatory Arnold Palmer teebox swinging a 7 iron off a borrowed set of clubs feom the wonderful @triciaclar33 family (who had a birthday very recently happy birthday Trish!) and in all likelihood I was probably wearing something half ridiculous.
—
Nevertheless, I connected on that thing like a deep line drive off the center field wall and there was no doubt about it once it hit the green and rolled 30-40 feet uphill and straight into the hole. 
—
I’ll never forget it. It was an ecstatic, collective eruption of so many different emotions that was acknowledged by groupings holes away as we stampeded loudly and in disbelief around the lake, up the approach and onto the green to get this ball sitting in the hole on 7 on a beautiful summer night. 
—
@tetonpines crafted me a plaque to celebrate the achievement, one thatI never had any inclination to try and get—it just happened, and I am grateful for it.  Because now, when I happen to be at @tetongravity founder Steve Jones’ house and in the team clubhouse that is The Grateful Shed, I see that plaque he hung up on the wall and the rarity of that day becomes more apparent and special to me every time I do ✨
—
Now, where to hide this ball from myself again so I don’t take it out for another round 🙈
